Description: Fragment of neck and oval, tapering handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '190', circled. Name Aristogeitos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.15876.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (perhaps, but could also be an acquisition from Petrie.)
Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (if not a find by Newton; chipping rather suggests Petrie)
